Covid-19. JOHANNESBURG - The number of new infections is dropping with 1,004 new infections recorded. Sadly, four more people have died over the last 24 to 48 hours. READ: COVID-19 | NICD says SA is entering fourth wave Gauteng is leading in infections with 435 new cases recorded, followed by KwaZulu-Natal with 172 new infections and the Western Cape is sitting on 160 cases. The rest of the provinces have recorded less than 100 infections. Over 10,600 tests have been conducted with a positivity rate of 9.4-percent. #COVID19 UPDATE: 10,689 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs, with 1,004 new cases, which represents a 9.4% positivity rate. Today @HealthZA reports 16 deaths; of which 4 occurred in the past 24–48 hrs. Total fatalities are 101,162 to date: https://t.co/9dXFDOJhlo pic.twitter.com/xQav0jzUmt